result.formatted_address: Sang Fat Mansion, 218-220 Sai Yeung Choi St S, Prince Edward, Hong Kong
result.name: New Korean BBQ restaurant

reviews.text: Amazing service and great selection of food. Unlimited canned beer
The food is fresh and the price is resonable, just the buffet do not include drinks.
Quality of the food is good &  tastes good.

Server lady was very pushy and rude; kept trying to bully us into ordering a set lunch for 4 people when it was only my husband & myself dining. When I politely told her we needed a few more minutes to look through the menu, she just hovered over us and kept pushing the most expensive option on the menu. I should have known when we arrived at lunch time and were the only customers in the restaurant! I just had high hopes due to all the good reviews, but unfortunately we did not experience the same as some of the other reviewers. Lastly, the food did not outright give us food poisoning but it did upset our stomaches for a couple days after so... we won't be returning!

Came for lunch on a Saturday. It was not busy. Buffet was good. Meat, fish and squid. The squid were remarkably soft. Good price at hkd130 including service charge. Softdrinks and Beer included. Will probably be back again when I go back to HK
